Hello All

I've been through New Brewing Lager Beer a couple times now, and I've
learned a lot. I'm comfortable with a single decoction mash and intend
to try it out twice in the next brew session.

At the end of ch-14, he provides several simple recipes for lager
styles. Now, in these recipes (e.g. the Munich dark) he states:

Doughing-in: 8 quarts
Mashing-in: 5 quarts
Strike Temp: 155F

What are the water quantities for? Are they quantities of boiling water
to be used for a step/infusion mash?

This is probably a silly question, but I just want to be clear on
it. Since he leaves infusion mashes for the appendices, I'm confused
by the appearance of these numbers in the recipes.

Thanks,

JB

