For certain grain types the dough-in and mash-in have been collapsed
into one step. Noonan gives the protein test/calculation one can run
from the malt assay.

John: I know a decoction isn't strictly required, but I want to try it
anyway. IMO a single decoction is not much more work than a step mash,
maybe even less. I'm just curious. It's my intention to do (in the
future) a specific beer formulation twice in one session - one with a
simple infusion, and one with a single decoction, and compare.

I'm not in the least bit interested in doing a double or triple
decoction, though :-)

