Yeah, that's actually how I do it too.  I "dough in" with around 115F water,
roll my sleeves up and knead the grains by hand to make sure it all gets
wetted and there aren't any dough balls.  Then I add another shot of boiling
strike water (aka "mash in") to raise it up to my mash temp.

That's probably what Noonan is talking about.  IE, they're not really
seperate rests as part of a multi-step infusion, but rather just a
way of adding your initial strike water.

John.
