Keep in mind that protein rests are usually not necessary with most
fully modified malts we have today.  You used to be able to get
undermodified malt which required it, but it's really difficult to
even find that stuff these days.  I don't dough in for protein reasons,
I just do it because I find it easier than trying to stir the mash in
order to get rid of clumps and/or dough balls, etc.

